<item>
            <title>[LU-10478] Use ZFS RPMs from zfsonlinux.org for building Lustre</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10478</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Instead of building our own ZFS RPMs in order to build our own Lustre packages and for testing, it makes sense to fetch (with cache) and use pre-built ZFS RPMs from zfsonlinux.org.  Beyond the minor savings of reducing the building on our own systems, more importantly this ensures that the packages we are building (i.e. &lt;tt&gt;lustre-osd-zfs-mount&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;kmod-lustre-osd-zfs&lt;/tt&gt;) will be based on exactly the same packages as what users will install.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will also simplify the integration of Lustre with Linux distros that already include ZFS packages, such as Ubuntu 16.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="46412">LU-10478</key>
